{"id": "1482743333041344623", "channel_id": "1482743333041344623", "type": 0, "author_id": "212587018436345856", "author_name": "nactra", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hello, i'm grateful for the features allowing background and BGM customization - but having the same BGM all the time, no matter what it is, gets repetitive.\n\nSuggestion is simple: allow to pick more than one selection for Bakcgrounds and BGMs, with set or randomized rotation.", "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:12:38.636000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 10}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1482743333041344623", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Idle BGM multipick", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1482727556003139635", "channel_id": "1482727556003139635", "type": 0, "author_id": "195401302145105920", "author_name": "jollysquire", "author_bot": false, "content": "It would be nice if either:\n1) You edited the main page so that a screenshot contains all 5 waves\n2) Introduce a \"Share\" button that generates an image that contains all of your clears.\n\nIt's cool seeing people sharing clears but needing two screenshots to do so could be a nice improvement when you have the time to rework it.", "timestamp": "2026-03-15T13:09:57.097000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👆", "emoji_id": null, "count": 6}, {"emoji": "💯", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [{"id": "1482727556418371668", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 2084472, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1482727556003139635/1482727556418371668/image.png?ex=69fb3da5&is=69f9ec25&hm=da502225fd02e47dbffa5beb383b38786a7686038e64ba22877a2f3d1f1d6004&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1482727556003139635", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Make D-Tide a single screenshot", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1482702865041588315", "channel_id": "1482702865041588315", "type": 0, "author_id": "381607726209564684", "author_name": "sonatadocantora", "author_bot": false, "content": "There are several characters that could benefit from small adjustments or tweaks to improve their individual power. However, among all of them, there is one character that feels like she is at the very bottom of the roster, and that character is Wanda.\n\nWanda is possibly the only Counter archetype character that feels completely wasted. Her ability to generate permanent counter is mediocre, her cards come with negative AP value, and the actual value she provides depends far too much on investment compared to what the character realistically offers.\n\nOne of the biggest problems when trying to view Wanda as a defensive character is that her defensive value and team contribution are practically nonexistent around 80% of the time. Unless you have Overexalt, she cannot consistently reduce enemy power.\n\nHer card that should theoretically be one of her stronger tools ends up feeling underwhelming. It drains your arithmetic resources and cannot reduce its own cost, which makes it inefficient unless you already have excess arithmetic available.\n\nHer only offensive card scales with the amount of counter generated, which is unfortunate because Wanda herself is not good at generating counter in the first place.\n\nIt is honestly disappointing to see a character with such a good concept end up being almost the weakest character in the very archetype where she should be the queen.\n\nIf you compare her to other counter characters, the gap becomes very clear.\n\n** Other Counter Characters**\n\n**Caecus:**\nCaecus can generate an absurd amount of ***permanent counter***, even without being built as a full DPS.\nHe can also deal significantly higher damage through counter interactions and tentacle mechanics, while also providing healing. Meanwhile, Wanda struggles to even reach half of the counter that a simple Caecus can generate in a single turn. On top of that, Wanda needs her passive just to produce a small shield.", "timestamp": "2026-03-15T11:31:50.313000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "wanda_proud", "emoji_id": "1468258146551333088", "count": 20}, {"emoji": "approved", "emoji_id": "1356053028787982558", "count": 11}, {"emoji": "Ramona_love", "emoji_id": "1459077541829546007", "count": 1}, {"emoji": "ramona_wisdom", "emoji_id": "1468258669341966452", "count": 1}, {"emoji": "👆", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [{"id": "1482702865490514051", "filename": "Wanda.webp", "content_type": "image/webp", "size": 52930, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1482702865041588315/1482702865490514051/Wanda.webp?ex=69fb26a6&is=69f9d526&hm=c8ebcc639fe818cf92cc07d63a079f79c1e62ed8bd7dff58cc4cf7ce998e7459&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1482702865041588315", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Possibly an unpopular opinion", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497", "1361168939622727801"]}
